[[include component:image-block | name=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9d/A_man_using_a_urinal.jpg | caption=Victim of SCP-XXXX]]

**Special Containment Procedures:** Hidden security cameras monitor Foundation-owned and high-traffic public restrooms. Individuals suspected to have ingested SCP-XXXX are to be transferred to the nearest Foundation site, where they undergo Operation Dehydration.

Specialty centrifuges are installed in both public-sector and Foundation-owned water treatment facilities, where SCP-XXXX is filtered into an on-site vat [[footnote]] Vat capacity should hold at least 5,000 litres. [[/footnote]]. Each vat is assigned at least two D-Class personnel, of mutually exclusive language proficiencies, as well as a supervising researcher. The D-Class personnel are to consume SCP-XXXX, and the supervisor assumes the full-time responsibility for the continuous enactment of Operation Dehydration. 

The following containment procedures are conditionally executed, until a time when Dr. Nations deems that SCP-XXXX's global frequency has been limited to an acceptable degree [[footnote]] Current heuristic is 86 civilian manifestations per year. [[/footnote]].
* SCP-XXXX is provided as drinking water to D-Class personnel. Wardens are to enforce that these personnel enter restrooms in groups of mutually exclusive language proficiencies.
* SCP-XXXX is publicly advertised and sold as healthy bottled water for infants.
* Automated tasers are installed in Foundation restrooms.

Personnel assigned to SCP-XXXX may request a site transfer after twelve weeks of service.

**Description:** SCP-XXXX is an anomalous variant of water, with a density of 985kg/m3 [[footnote]] For reference, the density of water is 997 kg/m3 [[/footnote]] at room temperature. Once ingested by a human, SCP-XXXX's anomalous effects manifest upon their entry into a populated restroom.

A successful manifestation compels all present individuals to use adjacent toilets and engage in pleasant conversation, with a strong tendency to expose personal information. Throughout the conversation, SCP-XXXX would self-replicate in each individual's urinary system to sustain the discharge of urine. In most recorded cases, the total discharge far exceeds the capacity of a human bladder.

Urinary excretion wanes as the conversation naturally concludes, signalling the end of the manifestation. Interviews with affected subjects afterward report that they aren't troubled by their anomalous urinary performance.

In the event where SCP-XXXX attempts to manifest, but the individuals involved are unable to verbally communicate, the volume of SCP-XXXX in their bladders is neutralised into non-anomalous water upon urination.

**Addendum:** The following logs are a representative sample of incidents caused by SCP-XXXX. For access to the full collection, consult Dr. Nations.

