[[div class="blockquote"]]
= **Incident XXXX.2352**
= Private Bathroom, Site 19 F-6 

Department Director H. Silva enters her office bathroom. An unidentified man steps out of a locker, decloaks his camotech and holsters his firearm. They discuss origami techniques, before being interrupted by on-site security.

||~ Participant ||~ Duration (s) ||~ Est. Volume (ml) ||~ Est. Constituent SCP-XXXX ||
|| Dir. Silva || 36 || 432 || 6.54% ||
|| Man || 35 || 490 || 0% ||

**Addendum:** The man has been identified as a Chaos Insurgency operative, detained and scheduled for interrogation.
----

= [ DEBRIEFING LOG ]

**Agent Bravo:** Sorry about that ma'am. We'll get you cleaned up.

**Dir. Silva:** Why. The hell. Are there //tasers// in my toilet.

**Agent Bravo:** New site protocol while you were on sabbatical. Handed down by O-██.

**Dir. Silva:** What? Okay, well let's get into that later. Help me up.

**Agent Bravo:** Negative on that order. I must remain outside the boundaries of this restroom.

**Dir. Silva:** What about that unconscious gentleman in the shower? He has a //gun//.

**Agent Bravo:** He's fairly harmless while you remain in the bathroom. We'll retrieve him after the drone arrives to fetch you for Operation Dehydration.

**Dir. Silva:** Operation what?

[[/div]]



[[div class="experiment"]]
[[=]]
+++ OPERATION DEHYDRATION - Foreword
[[/=]]

I know most of you complained once you were assigned to SCP-XXXX. Look, I get it, studying urine isn't anyone's cup of tea. Just suck it up. You're given the option to rotate out after 3 months anyway. There are far worse things you could be doing in the Foundation. 

Worse things such as Operation Dehydration. Unfortunately, it's the most reliable method we've got to keep manifestation numbers down. For some reason the skip turns to regular water if the people can't speak. Took us forever to figure that one out. So we've arranged for some special D-Class to act as water purifiers, and you'll be making sure they're peeing right, 8 hours a day. Same applies if a civilian wanders to a toilet and starts announcing their life story. We snatch them and flush SCP-XXXX from their system. Give 'em plenty of water - regular water - to speed up the process.

Some of you might ask, what's the point? Why go to such lengths to stop a bit of gossiping? Well just like gossip, this piss spreads. And spreads fast. Worst case: LK-Class scenario. Elimination of privacy, and our precious veil becomes as flimsy as soggy toilet paper. On top of that, each manifestation effectively grows the volume of water on Earth, a net increase in global sea levels. So unless you want to drown the planet in humanity's piss, do your job.

[[>]]
//- Dr. Y. Nations//
[[/>]]

----

= [BEGIN VIDEO LOG]

Pi: Are you ready to begin [REDACTED]?
[REDACTED]: Give me a moment. I just woke up, so it's hard.
Pi: ...
[REDACTED]: ...
D-3523: ...
Pi: Have you calmed down?
[REDACTED]: Uhh, kinda.
Pi: Proceed.
//[REDACTED] and D-4421 start doing their business.//
D-3523: ...
[REDACTED]: ...
Pi: Flow is at a steady 14ml/s.
[REDACTED] ...
D-3523: ...
[REDACTED] ...
D-3523: Hey, watch it! (in Greek)
Nations: Spillage identified.  Please aim your discharge.
[REDACTED]: Sorry.
D-3523: ...
[REDACTED] ...
Pi: Total volume measures 229.6ml. Elapsed time is 16.4s. Is that alright, Yuri?
Nations: Yes, it is within acceptable parameters.
[REDACTED]: So, when can I go home?
Nations: Based on your historical metrics, we require another 57 iterations before you're cleared.

[[/div]]

Researcher put on administrative leave after exposing janitor to information beyond their clearance. D-Class have their tongues cut to avoid speaking.

Entire town succumbs to SCP-XXXX. Not feasible to evacuate entire population to a Foundation facility, so Operation Hydration is attempted on-site. They realise that higher density people are no longer able to pee by themselves.

